enable dev mode to get a terminal
Settings -> Security {???} -> Dev Mode
phone will restart after it is done installing
you can just wait {about 2 minutes} once it prompts for:
  ~2.6MB additional installation required

open a terminal:
devel-su #password is rootme
passwd user #any password

on n9:
insert usb,
select: sync and connect

on pc:
sudo ifconfig usb0 192.168.2.14 netmask 255.255.255.0 up
scp ssh-config user@192.168.2.15:/tmp
ssh user@192.168.2.15

devel-su #rootme
sh /tmp/ssh-config

0) dev mode + ssh-config
1) set-host
2) keygen.pl
3) install-sane
4) config-files
5) install-packages
